WEBVTT

00:01.222 --> 00:03.214
ALL RIGHT.
HOW DID I DO?

00:03.214 --> 00:04.218
LET'S SEE.

00:04.218 --> 00:07.219
SINE "X" PLUS THE SQUARE ROOT
OF NEGATIVE TWO.

00:07.219 --> 00:10.231
AND THE SURVEY SAYS...
[ BELL RINGS ]

00:10.231 --> 00:13.234
MOM, YOU MAKE TRIG
SO MUCH FUN.
AW, THANK YOU.

00:13.234 --> 00:15.231
OKAY, SEND IN WARREN
WITH HIS HOMEWORK.

00:15.231 --> 00:17.233
OKAY. MWAH!
TELL HIM TO HURRY.

00:17.233 --> 00:20.231
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

00:20.231 --> 00:22.248
WHY DO I FEEL LIKE WE'RE ALWAYS
BUYING TOILET PAPER?

00:22.248 --> 00:24.254
[ CHUCKLES ]
BECAUSE BERT AND HILLARY

00:24.254 --> 00:27.238
LIKE WRAPPING WARREN UP
LIKE A MUMMY.

00:27.238 --> 00:28.250
[ CELLPHONE ALERT BLARES ]

00:28.250 --> 00:29.262
AH, CRAP.
WHAT?

00:29.262 --> 00:32.253
IT'S DIANE. SHE WANTS TO KNOW
IF WE CAN DO CARPOOL ON MONDAY.

00:32.253 --> 00:34.250
NO! WE CAN'T!
WE'VE GOT NOTHING MONDAY.

00:34.250 --> 00:36.260
I GOT WORK.
YEAH, BUT BESIDES THAT,
WE HAVE NOTHING.

00:36.260 --> 00:37.264
JUST TELL HER
WE'RE BUSY.

00:37.264 --> 00:39.254
SHE'LL KNOW I'M LYING.
SHE ALWAYS KNOWS.

00:39.254 --> 00:41.272
I'LL DO IT.
I'M A GREAT LIAR.

00:41.272 --> 00:44.275
[ CELLPHONE ALERT BLARES ]
OH, COME ON!

00:44.275 --> 00:47.258
SHE'S GOT
AN EMERGENCY ACL PROCEDURE.

00:47.258 --> 00:49.260
IT'S JUST KNEE SURGERY.

00:49.260 --> 00:51.265
NOBODY'S EVERY DIED
IN KNEE SURGERY.

00:51.265 --> 00:52.281
[ CELLPHONE ALERT BLARES ]

00:54.286 --> 00:56.270
WHAT AM I LOOKING AT?

00:56.270 --> 00:58.273
IT'S A WEB LINK FOR PEOPLE
WHO HAVE DIED IN KNEE SURGERY.

01:03.295 --> 01:04.297
OH, MY GOD.

01:04.297 --> 01:07.280
I SAW THIS
IN A HORROR MOVIE ONCE.

01:07.280 --> 01:08.289
IT WAS A SLUMBER PARTY,

01:08.289 --> 01:10.291
AND THE KILLER WAS CALLING
FROM INSIDE THE HOUSE.

01:10.291 --> 01:13.287
SHE CAN'T BE
IN THE HOUSE.

01:13.287 --> 01:14.295
CAN'T I?

01:14.295 --> 01:15.307
[ SCREAMS ]

01:16.298 --> 01:20.294
AND NOW THAT I KNOW
YOU'RE FREE, I'LL ASK AGAIN.

01:20.294 --> 01:21.304
CAN YOU DO CARPOOL
ON MONDAY?

01:21.304 --> 01:24.297
PETER! RIGHT NOW!

01:24.297 --> 01:25.308
YOU ARE DOING CARPOOL MONDAY

01:25.308 --> 01:27.307
AND THE NEXT THREE MONDAYS
FOR LYING TO ME!

01:28.301 --> 01:31.304
THAT FELT GREAT. I PUT HER
ON TOP OF THE RECYCLING BIN.

01:31.304 --> 01:32.315
GOOD, BABE.
YEAH.

01:32.315 --> 01:34.309
WHAT IF SOMEONE STEALS
THE LAPTOP, THOUGH?

01:34.309 --> 01:35.329
THEN DIANE BECOMES
THEIR PROBLEM.

01:35.329 --> 01:37.313
WHO CARES?
LETS' GET OUT OF HERE.

01:40.322 --> 01:43.325
MOM?
I BROUGHT MY HOMEWORK.

01:43.325 --> 01:45.334
UH...WARREN.

01:45.334 --> 01:48.332
WARREN!
I'M OUTSIDE!

01:48.332 --> 01:50.322
OH. COOL. WELL,
I'LL BE IN MY ROOM.

01:50.322 --> 01:52.329
JUST LET ME KNOW
WHEN YOU'RE READY TO START.

01:52.329 --> 01:55.326
OH! YES! TWO‐PLY!
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:58.329 --> 02:01.334
♪♪♪

02:08.346 --> 02:10.342
PETE: KATE?

02:12.343 --> 02:14.345
KATE?

02:14.345 --> 02:16.350
[ MUNCHING ]

02:16.350 --> 02:18.354
[ KATE MOANS ]

02:22.353 --> 02:24.355
WHAT ARE WE DOING?

02:24.355 --> 02:25.360
I TRY TO BE A REALLY
GOOD EXAMPLE TO THE KIDS,

02:25.360 --> 02:27.381
BUT SOMETIMES I JUST WANT
CHIPS BEFORE DINNER.

02:27.381 --> 02:29.363
OH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
SURE.

02:29.363 --> 02:30.374
IF YOU EVER WANT SOME,
I ALWAYS KEEP A BAG

02:30.374 --> 02:31.384
BEHIND
THE BIG JUG OF BLEACH.

02:33.373 --> 02:35.366
IF YOU'RE NOT TOO FULL
ON BLEACH CHIPS

02:35.366 --> 02:36.371
AND YOU'RE STILL HUNGRY,

02:36.371 --> 02:38.374
I GOT US LAST‐MINUTE
RESERVATIONS AT VOULOIR.

02:38.374 --> 02:40.372
[ GASPS ]

02:40.372 --> 02:42.374
QUOI?

02:42.374 --> 02:44.376
THAT'S FRENCH
FOR "WHAT?!"

02:44.376 --> 02:47.380
IT'S TIME. NO MORE FISH STICKS,
NO MORE HOT DOGS.

02:47.380 --> 02:50.385
TONIGHT WE'RE GONNA EAT LIKE
REAL, ACTUAL, GROWNUP PEOPLE.

02:50.385 --> 02:52.401
WOW! I LOVE IT!
WAIT. WHAT ABOUT THE KIDS?

02:52.401 --> 02:54.389
I GOT IT COVERED.
JACKIE'S GONNA BABYSIT.

02:54.389 --> 02:58.389
HOW MUCH DOES SHE CHARGE?
HALF OF EVERYTHING I OWN.

02:58.389 --> 02:59.393
MAN, HOW DO I GET
A DEAL LIKE THAT?

02:59.393 --> 03:01.402
YOU DON'T.
YOU'RE MARRIED TO ME.
BUMMER.

03:01.402 --> 03:02.414
BUT I'M GONNA TAKE YOU OUT,
I'M GONNA WINE YOU,

03:02.414 --> 03:05.405
I'M GONNA DINE YOU, I'M GONNA
KEEP YOU OUT TILL 10:00.

03:05.405 --> 03:06.416
WHOA.

03:06.416 --> 03:08.418
[ SIGHS ]
[ CELLPHONE ALERT BLARES ]

03:08.418 --> 03:10.420
THAT'S DIANE.
OKAY, WAIT.

03:10.420 --> 03:12.404
IF SHE WANTS ANYTHING,
JUST TELL HER

03:12.404 --> 03:13.425
THAT WE WERE
IN A BANK ROBBERY TODAY.

03:13.425 --> 03:16.408
THEN I GOT CARJACKED.
[ CELLPHONE ALERT BLARES ]

03:16.408 --> 03:19.411
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!
TELL HER MY COUSIN WAS MURDERED.

03:19.411 --> 03:21.424
WHAT? I DON'T LIKE
MY COUSINS THAT MUCH.

03:21.424 --> 03:22.435
THAT'S CREEPY.
THAT WEIRDED ME OUT.

03:22.435 --> 03:24.432
YOU SHOULD TALK
TO SOMEBODY ABOUT THAT.

03:24.432 --> 03:27.430
[ CELLPHONE ALERT BLARES ]
HELLO. DIANE. WHAT'S UP?

03:27.430 --> 03:28.441
HI. PETER.

03:28.441 --> 03:31.443
I'M GONNA NEED YOUR HELP WITH
THE SCHOOL FUNDRAISER TONIGHT.

03:31.443 --> 03:33.431
UH...OKAY.

03:33.431 --> 03:35.448
I'LL DONATE WHATEVER
YOU'RE DONATING, PLUS A DOLLAR.

03:35.448 --> 03:37.430
NO, I'M GONNA NEED YOU
IN PERSON, PETER.

03:37.430 --> 03:39.434
A LOT OF PEOPLE
DROPPED OUT ON ME.

03:39.434 --> 03:42.442
I GUESS BANNING BEER
[SCOFFS] FROM OKTOBERFEST

03:42.442 --> 03:43.448
MADE A LOT
OF REAL ENEMIES.

03:43.448 --> 03:46.449
WELL, I'D LOVE TO
PITCH IN TONIGHT, BUT ‐‐

03:46.449 --> 03:49.449
GREAT, THANK YOU.
NO, KATE AND I
ARE GOING OUT TO DINNER.

03:49.449 --> 03:51.448
THAT'S FINE.
BRING HER, TOO.

03:51.448 --> 03:53.455
YOU'RE NOT UNDERSTANDING ME
AT ALL.

03:53.455 --> 03:55.467
OH, I THINK I UNDERSTAND
PERFECTLY NOW.

03:55.467 --> 03:58.454
I JUST WISH THAT, UH,
YOUR CHILDREN'S FUTURE

03:58.454 --> 04:02.456
WAS AS IMPORTANT TO YOU AS,
YOU KNOW, A FUSSY DINNER

04:02.456 --> 04:04.460
AND, "OH, WHAT CAN I DO WITH
A BRUSSEL SPROUT THESE DAYS?"

04:04.460 --> 04:05.469
IT'S OKAY.

04:05.469 --> 04:07.477
THERE'S OTHER FATHERS WHO
WILL BE THERE FOR THEIR KIDS.

04:09.466 --> 04:12.465
WHAT TIME?
I'LL NEED YOU STAT.

04:12.465 --> 04:14.472
JUST REMEMBER ‐‐
IT'S A THEMED FUNDRAISER,

04:14.472 --> 04:16.475
SO COME
AS YOUR FAVORITE '80S ICON.

04:16.475 --> 04:18.476
GREAT. I'LL COME
AS THE BERLIN WALL.

04:18.476 --> 04:22.475
THERE'S NO TIME FOR JOKING.
I'LL SEE YOU SHORTLY.
MARGARET THATCHER.

04:22.475 --> 04:23.492
WOW, BABE!
VERY IMPRESSIVE.

04:23.492 --> 04:26.488
YOU HELD FIRM
FOR ALMOST TWO SENTENCES.

04:26.488 --> 04:28.483
WHAT KIND OF AN EMERGENCY
WAS IT THIS TIME,

04:28.483 --> 04:31.485
A NEURO‐OPTIC
PLASMADECTAMOSCOPY?

04:31.485 --> 04:32.505
MY CHILDREN'S FUTURE.

04:32.505 --> 04:35.508
I PROMISE,
I'LL MAKE IT UP TO YOU.
FINE.

04:35.508 --> 04:37.489
BUT I'M TELLING YOU ‐‐

04:37.489 --> 04:38.509
SHOULD HAVE GONE
WITH THE MURDERED COUSIN.

04:38.509 --> 04:39.512
YOU'RE SCARING ME.
♪ THEY GOT THE BEAT ♪

04:39.512 --> 04:42.498
♪ THEY GOT THE BEAT ♪

04:42.498 --> 04:44.504
♪ THEY GOT THE BEAT ♪

04:44.504 --> 04:46.506
♪ YEAH, THEY GOT THE BEAT ♪

04:46.506 --> 04:48.508
[ LAUGHTER ]

04:48.508 --> 04:51.507
WHAT IS IT WITH PARENTS
AND THEME PARTIES?

04:51.507 --> 04:53.516
THEY'RE TRYING TO GET BACK
TO A TIME WHEN THEY WERE HAPPY.

04:53.516 --> 04:55.523
WELL,
SHOOT ME WHEN I'M 40.

04:55.523 --> 04:56.525
I MEAN 50.

04:56.525 --> 04:58.525
I MEAN ‐‐ I'LL STOP.

04:58.525 --> 05:00.525
PETER, FINALLY.

05:00.525 --> 05:01.526
HEY.
DIANE.

05:01.526 --> 05:04.518
YOU LOOK GREAT.
WHO ARE YOU?

05:04.518 --> 05:05.526
OH, COME ON, KATE.

05:05.526 --> 05:06.536
YOU GOT THIS.

05:06.536 --> 05:08.524
UH...

05:08.524 --> 05:09.543
HIT ME
WITH YOUR BEST SHOT.

05:09.543 --> 05:11.525
♪ YEAH, THEY GO THE BEAT ♪

05:11.525 --> 05:13.528
SPOCK.
NO.

05:13.528 --> 05:15.539
BLANCHE FROM
"THE GOLDEN GIRLS"?

05:15.539 --> 05:18.533
PAT BENATAR.
OH.

05:18.533 --> 05:21.541
AND, UH, LET ME GUESS. YOU'RE
BILLY IDOL, AND YOU ARE...

05:21.541 --> 05:24.537
MELANIE GRIFFITH.
"WORKING GIRL" FROM THE '80S.

05:24.537 --> 05:25.541
YES, WELL,
IT'S NICE TO SEE YOU

05:25.541 --> 05:26.553
FINALLY DRESSED UP
LIKE AN ADULT.
THANK YOU.

05:26.553 --> 05:28.560
UM, PETER, I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO INTRODUCE ME ONSTAGE

05:28.560 --> 05:31.548
LATER ON TONIGHT, SO I'VE
WRITTEN OUT SOME TALKING POINTS.

05:31.548 --> 05:33.564
DON'T YOU JUST WANT ME
TO TELL THEM YOU'RE BETTER
THAN EVERYONE ELSE?

05:33.564 --> 05:35.555
YES, BUT I'D LIKE
FOR IT TO SOUND NATURAL.

05:35.555 --> 05:37.557
PLEASE GO HELP PATTY
STOCK THE BAR.

05:37.557 --> 05:39.558
AND WHAT CAN YOU DO?

05:39.558 --> 05:40.574
I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT CAN YOU DO?

05:40.574 --> 05:42.561
OH, MAYBE YOU COULD
HELP THE CATERERS

05:42.561 --> 05:43.572
WITH THE VEGETABLE PLATTERS.

05:45.560 --> 05:48.563
THANK YOU AGAIN FOR COMING.
I'LL BE AT THE BAR.

05:48.563 --> 05:51.565
IF YOU NEED SOME LIQUOR,
I'M YOUR MAN.

05:51.565 --> 05:55.570
UGH. THIS BLOWS.

05:55.570 --> 05:57.591
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE BEEN TOSSED
AROUND AND 'ROUND ♪

05:57.591 --> 05:59.578
♪ YEAH, YEAH, YEAH ♪

05:59.578 --> 06:01.588
MRS. STEINBERG! HI!

06:01.588 --> 06:04.591
I LOVE YOUR COSTUME.
WHO ARE YOU?

06:04.591 --> 06:06.595
OH, UH, I'M JUST ME.

06:06.595 --> 06:10.604
NO ONE TOLD ME
IT WAS A THEME PARTY.

06:10.604 --> 06:13.606
YOU ‐‐ I MEAN,
YOU LOOK AMAZING.

06:13.606 --> 06:15.601
JUST GORGEOUS.

06:15.601 --> 06:18.590
ANYWAY, UH, LISTEN,
SO DIANE WANTED US

06:18.590 --> 06:21.607
TO SWITCH JOBS TODAY,
SO YOU ARE ON VEGETABLES.

06:21.607 --> 06:25.599
OH, DID SHE NOT LIKE
THE WAY I MADE THE PUNCH?

06:25.599 --> 06:27.611
WOMAN:
WHAT? I CAN'T HEAR YOU.
GUESS NOT.

06:28.616 --> 06:30.609
THERE IS COW MILK
IN THIS FRIDGE.

06:30.609 --> 06:32.613
I MEAN, HELLO?
WHERE'S THE LLAMA MILK?

06:32.613 --> 06:34.625
AND ONLY ONE KIND
OF HUMMUS?

06:34.625 --> 06:38.609
OH, OF COURSE.
LITTLE‐LADY MARGARITAS.

06:38.609 --> 06:40.617
REAL CLASSY, KATE.
OH, THAT'S DAD'S.

06:40.617 --> 06:44.622
WELL, EITHER WAY, THESE THINGS
ARE JUST LOADED WITH CHEMICALS.

06:44.622 --> 06:47.640
YEAH, DEFINITELY.

06:47.640 --> 06:49.623
HEY, MOM!

06:49.623 --> 06:52.630
SET THE TIMER FOR MY ONE HOUR
AND TWO MINUTES OF TV TIME?

06:52.630 --> 06:53.642
OH, HON,
YOU ONLY GET AN HOUR.

06:53.642 --> 06:56.631
BUT I NEED TIME TO GET
COMFORTABLE AND FOR PEE BREAKS.

06:56.631 --> 06:58.652
OH, SWEETIE!
YOU ARE SUCH A PLANNER.

06:58.652 --> 07:02.634
WILL YOU PROMISE ME YOU WON'T
FORGET TO LET YOURSELF FAIL?

07:03.656 --> 07:06.647
WHEW. WOW.
THAT JUST GOT REAL.

07:06.647 --> 07:08.654
MY TURN. CHELSEA CLINTON
IS LIVE CHATTING.

07:08.654 --> 07:10.644
AND I WANT TO ASK HER
HOW SHE BALANCES IT ALL.

07:10.644 --> 07:11.660
OH,
I WOULD LOVE TO HELP,

07:11.660 --> 07:13.662
BUT THIS HORSE AND THIS CAT
ARE BEST FRIENDS.

07:13.662 --> 07:15.651
[ HORSE WHINNIES ]

07:15.651 --> 07:16.659
GO USE JACKIE'S.

07:16.659 --> 07:21.655
[ SIGHS ]
OH, MAN. WHAT IS THIS?

07:21.655 --> 07:23.657
WARREN, COME HERE.
IT'S SOME KIND OF DATING SITE.

07:23.657 --> 07:26.660
[ CLICK ]
OH. HELLO.

07:26.660 --> 07:28.662
IF YOU'VE STUMBLED
UPON MY PROFILE,

07:28.662 --> 07:30.664
THEN I ALREADY KNOW
THAT YOU LIKE YOGA,

07:30.664 --> 07:32.683
TUVAN THROAT SINGERS,
AND NASCAR.

07:32.683 --> 07:34.682
[ GROANS ]
BUT NOW'S YOUR CHANCE
TO JOURNEY

07:34.682 --> 07:36.669
JUST A LITTLE FARTHER
WITH ME.

07:36.669 --> 07:38.669
SO COME ON!

07:38.669 --> 07:39.675
WHERE DOES SHE WANT US
TO GO?

07:44.682 --> 07:45.693
[ MUSIC PLAYS IN DISTANCE ]

07:45.693 --> 07:46.698
[ SIGHS ]

07:48.681 --> 07:49.702
WAY TO GO ‐‐
GETTING US CUP DUTY.

07:49.702 --> 07:51.687
IF WE'RE
NOT GONNA HAVE FUN,

07:51.687 --> 07:52.699
AT LEAST WE CAN
NOT HAVE FUN TOGETHER.

07:52.699 --> 07:55.692
I CAN'T BELIEVE WE HAD TO
CANCEL OUR PLANS TO CARRY CUPS.

07:55.692 --> 07:56.698
I THINK WE OWE IT
TO OURSELVES

07:56.698 --> 07:59.690
TO AT LEAST TRY THEM OUT,
DON'T YOU?

07:59.690 --> 08:01.707
WOW. GOT ANYTHING ELSE
IN THERE?

08:01.707 --> 08:03.709
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I DO.

08:03.709 --> 08:04.715
IT'S NOT VOULOIR,

08:04.715 --> 08:06.712
BUT AT LEAST IT'S JUST
THE TWO OF US DOWN HERE.

08:06.712 --> 08:08.706
I'M NOT GONNA LET DIANE
RUIN OUR NIGHT.

08:08.706 --> 08:10.723
WE GOT HALF AN HOUR.
WHAT DID YOU HAVE IN MIND?

08:10.723 --> 08:15.706
A LITTLE WINE, A LITTLE CHEESE,
A LITTLE...YOU KNOW.

08:15.706 --> 08:16.708
REALLY?

08:16.708 --> 08:17.730
SCHOOL'S
ALWAYS MADE ME HORNY.

08:17.730 --> 08:19.730
OH. SURE.
YEAH. ME TOO.

08:19.730 --> 08:21.717
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

08:25.719 --> 08:27.736
MM.
DO THAT AGAIN, YOU'LL BE
DANCING WITH YOURSELF.

08:27.736 --> 08:29.724
[ DRUMMING ]

08:31.737 --> 08:33.744
WELL, THAT'S THE END
OF THE SONG

08:33.744 --> 08:35.728
"NO, THAT'S NOT
MY ELEPHANT."

08:35.728 --> 08:36.747
WELL?
[ BOTH GASP ]

08:36.747 --> 08:39.736
PRETTY GOOD, RIGHT?
DON'T YOU THINK?

08:39.736 --> 08:41.737
UH...DO YOU WANT US
TO TELL YOU

08:41.737 --> 08:43.742
WHAT YOU WANT TO HEAR
OR TELL YOU THE TRUTH?

08:43.742 --> 08:44.752
OH, TELL ME
WHAT I WANT TO HEAR.

08:44.752 --> 08:46.759
OH! IT'S AWESOME!

08:46.759 --> 08:49.762
I MEAN, YOU ARE GOING TO FIND
THE MAN OF YOUR DREAMS.

08:49.762 --> 08:52.758
FANTASTIC.
OH! I KNEW IT. I KNEW IT!

08:52.758 --> 08:54.750
BUT IT IS
A LITTLE LONG.

08:54.750 --> 08:56.748
HUH.
AND HAS A LOT OF THOUGHTS.

08:56.748 --> 08:57.761
HMM.

08:57.761 --> 09:00.760
AND ‐‐ AND MAYBE THREE
TOO MANY IMPRESSIONS.
FOUR.

09:00.760 --> 09:01.766
WELL...

09:01.766 --> 09:02.777
[ AS FOGHORN LEGHORN ]
I SAY, I SAY, I SAY,

09:02.777 --> 09:05.765
YOU CAN NEVER
HAVE ENOUGH IMPRESSIONS.

09:05.765 --> 09:06.770
[ IMITATES LASER FIRE ]

09:08.768 --> 09:10.783
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]
YEAH, THAT ‐‐
THAT'S FUN STUFF.

09:10.783 --> 09:12.785
YEAH.
HEY, I'VE GOT AN IDEA,
JACKIE.

09:12.785 --> 09:14.769
I COULD RE‐EDIT THIS
FOR YOU.

09:14.769 --> 09:15.789
HMM.
ZHUZH IT UP A LITTLE?

09:15.789 --> 09:18.789
YEAH! AND, UH,
I CAN HELP WITH YOUR WARDROBE.

09:18.789 --> 09:20.791
LET'S GO SEE WHAT KATE HAS
IN HER CLOSET.
YEAH.

09:20.791 --> 09:22.796
OKAY, YOU KNOW,
WE CAN TRY,

09:22.796 --> 09:24.783
BUT I THINK WE ALL KNOW
THAT KATE TAKES

09:24.783 --> 09:26.784
HER FASHION CUES
FROM THIS GAL.

09:26.784 --> 09:28.782
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:29.784 --> 09:31.796
WELL, THAT WAS
PRETTY ROCK 'N' ROLL.

09:31.796 --> 09:33.788
SMOKING‐HOT SEX
IN THE CLOSET,

09:33.788 --> 09:35.801
A LITTLE ARTISANAL
GOAT CHEESE.

09:35.801 --> 09:37.807
I THINK I'M MISSING
A SHOULDER PAD.

09:37.807 --> 09:39.794
OH, HERE.
I THOUGHT IT WAS MINE.

09:39.794 --> 09:40.799
THANKS, BABE.

09:40.799 --> 09:42.798
ALL RIGHT,
YOU WANT TO GRAB THE CUPS?
YEAH.

09:42.798 --> 09:44.798
I GOT TO GET UP THERE
AND INTRODUCE PAT BENATAR

09:44.798 --> 09:49.803
TO THE BREAKFAST CLUB
AND ABOUT A DOZEN JAMES SPADERS.

09:49.803 --> 09:51.814
OH, MY GOD.
THERE'S NO HANDLE.

09:51.814 --> 09:53.816
WHAT?
THERE'S NO HANDLE.

09:53.816 --> 09:56.809
ARE YOU SURE?
WAIT. LET ME CHECK
A THIRD TIME, OKAY?

09:56.809 --> 09:57.823
UH, NO. NO HANDLE.

09:57.823 --> 10:00.817
WE'RE RAISING MONEY
FOR A STUPID VEGETABLE GARDEN

10:00.817 --> 10:01.836
AND THE DOORS
DON'T HAVE ANY HANDLES?

10:01.836 --> 10:05.817
HELLO?
ANYBODY OUT THERE?

10:05.817 --> 10:07.833
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
UH, WE'RE IN
THE CLOSET HERE.

10:07.833 --> 10:09.825
[ POUNDING ON DOOR ]

10:09.825 --> 10:11.828
AND ONE OF US
REALLY HAS TO PEE!

10:14.840 --> 10:15.846
♪ KARMA, KARMA, KARMA, KARMA,
KARMA CHAMELEON ♪

10:15.846 --> 10:18.835
♪ YOU COME AND GO ♪
PETER, WHERE ARE YOU?

10:18.835 --> 10:19.836
[ SIGHS ]

10:19.836 --> 10:21.848
♪ YOU COME AND GO ♪

10:21.848 --> 10:22.853
PATTY.

10:22.853 --> 10:24.844
PETER HAS DISAPPEARED,

10:24.844 --> 10:26.842
SO I NEED YOU TO VOLUNTEER
TO INTRODUCE ME.

10:26.842 --> 10:27.843
OH, TO WHO?

10:28.846 --> 10:29.855
"TO WHOM."

10:29.855 --> 10:32.859
AND IT'S
THE ENTIRE AUDITORIUM.

10:32.859 --> 10:35.853
I'VE WRITTEN UP
SOME TALKING POINTS FOR PETER,

10:35.853 --> 10:37.862
SO JUST MAKE THEM
YOUR OWN, OKAY?

10:37.862 --> 10:41.870
UH, I‐I'M TERRIFIED
OF PUBLIC SPEAKING.

10:43.869 --> 10:47.860
OKAY.
I GUESS IT'S NOW OR NEVER.

10:47.860 --> 10:48.871
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]
IT'S NOW.

10:48.871 --> 10:50.878
I REALLY CAN'T.
TAKE A SIP.

10:50.878 --> 10:52.875
SIP? YEAH.
GOOD. COME ON.

10:52.875 --> 10:55.880
OKAY.
[ FEEDBACK ]

10:55.880 --> 11:00.878
HI. I'M PETER ‐‐
UM, PATTY STEINBERG.

11:00.878 --> 11:04.887
UM, MOST OF YOU KNOW ME
AS WARREN AND HILLARY'S FATH‐‐

11:04.887 --> 11:06.893
[ STAMMERS ]

11:06.893 --> 11:08.880
OHH.

11:08.880 --> 11:10.882
[ VOICE BREAKING ]
AND IT IS MY HONOR TO INTRODUCE

11:10.882 --> 11:14.897
THE CHAIR OF TONIGHT'S EVENT,
DR. DIANE BUCKLEY.

11:14.897 --> 11:15.903
[ APPLAUSE ]

11:15.903 --> 11:19.912
RENOWNED SURGEON,
TWO‐TIME SILVER MEDALIST

11:19.912 --> 11:24.907
IN THE 100‐METER BREASTSTROKE,
AND THE MOTHER OF MY CHILDREN.

11:24.907 --> 11:25.913
[ CROWD MURMURS ]

11:25.913 --> 11:27.911
[ CRYING ]
DIANE BUCKLEY.

11:27.911 --> 11:31.909
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN, THE
ALWAYS‐ECCENTRIC MRS. STEINBERG.

11:31.909 --> 11:32.914
YES, THANK YOU.

11:32.914 --> 11:33.921
GET IT TOGETHER, PATTY.
GET IT TOGETHER.

11:33.921 --> 11:34.917
OKAY.
THAT WASN'T SO BAD.

11:34.917 --> 11:36.930
WE ARE HERE TONIGHT
FOR ONE REASON ‐‐

11:36.930 --> 11:38.925
JOSEPH BROOKS HIGH SCHOOL.

11:38.925 --> 11:40.929
AND WITH
YOUR GENEROUS DONATIONS,

11:40.929 --> 11:43.926
WE CAN MAKE MUCH NEEDED
IMPROVEMENTS ON CAMPUS,

11:43.926 --> 11:49.938
SUCH AS A VEGETABLE GARDEN,
MORE HANDICAP RAMPS ON CAMPUS,

11:49.938 --> 11:51.940
EXTRA COUNSELING TO DEAL

11:51.940 --> 11:55.930
WITH THE RECENT RASH
OF TEEN PREGNANCIES.

11:55.930 --> 11:56.933
YOU GOT ANYTHING?

11:56.933 --> 11:57.941
NOPE. NOT A THING.

11:57.941 --> 11:59.931
[ SIGHS ]

11:59.931 --> 12:00.937
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

12:00.937 --> 12:01.955
I'M GONNA
JIMMY THE LOCK.

12:01.955 --> 12:03.947
DO YOU KNOW
HOW TO JIMMY?

12:03.947 --> 12:06.943
SURE. YOU JUST ‐‐

12:06.943 --> 12:07.958
THAT WAS
MY DRIVER'S LICENSE.

12:07.958 --> 12:09.943
[ GROANS ]

12:09.943 --> 12:11.959
GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

12:11.959 --> 12:12.965
[ SIGHS ]

12:14.958 --> 12:15.969
[ GRUNTS ]
[ METAL CLANGS ]

12:15.969 --> 12:18.953
OH! OOH!

12:18.953 --> 12:19.970
WHY DID YOU DO THAT?

12:19.970 --> 12:21.965
I DON'T KNOW.
I GOT TO PEE.

12:21.965 --> 12:22.976
HOW BAD?

12:22.976 --> 12:24.978
UH, SOMEWHERE BETWEEN
"BERT ON A HIGHWAY" BAD

12:24.978 --> 12:26.974
AND "WARREN IN A HOT TUB"
BAD.

12:26.974 --> 12:29.975
OH, MY GOD. HELP!

12:29.975 --> 12:31.965
[ CLANGING ]
HELP!

12:32.977 --> 12:34.984
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT ABOUT THIS?

12:34.984 --> 12:36.972
UH, YEAH. SURE.

12:36.972 --> 12:38.970
IF YOU HAVE A BODY
LIKE A 10‐YEAR‐OLD BOY.

12:38.970 --> 12:39.976
BUT UNLIKE KATE, SEE,

12:39.976 --> 12:41.985
I HAVE WOMEN'S BREASTS
AND A BUTT LIKE BEYONCÉ.

12:41.985 --> 12:42.992
OKAY.
OH, WAIT.

12:42.992 --> 12:44.994
WHO ARE YOU?!

12:44.994 --> 12:46.987
THIS IS NICE.

12:46.987 --> 12:47.998
THAT'S THE BED SPREAD.
SO?

12:47.998 --> 12:51.001
SEE THIS?
THIS WAS A TABLECLOTH ONCE.
YEAH.

12:51.001 --> 12:53.007
SO MUCH FOR THAT THANKSGIVING.
WON'T BE INVITED BACK.
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:53.007 --> 12:55.998
HEY, WHY DOESN'T SHE KEEP
THE SEWING MACHINE

12:55.998 --> 12:58.002
BY THE BED
LIKE A NORMAL PERSON?

12:58.002 --> 12:59.011
OH.
I DON'T KNOW.

12:59.011 --> 13:01.013
I NEED A B‐12 SHOT.

13:01.013 --> 13:03.997
SO, THIS IS ME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:03.997 --> 13:05.999
AND OVER HERE,

13:05.999 --> 13:11.013
WELL, I'VE LEFT JUST
A LITTLE BIT OF ROOM FOR YOU.

13:11.013 --> 13:13.011
WHAT'S THAT?

13:13.011 --> 13:15.008
OH, I‐I FOUND
SOME COOL EXPLOSION FOOTAGE

13:15.008 --> 13:16.018
I WANTED TO ADD
TO YOUR MOM'S VIDEO.

13:16.018 --> 13:18.016
WHY IS SHE
MAKING A VIDEO?

13:18.016 --> 13:19.030
TO MEET A MAN.

13:19.030 --> 13:20.033
WHY?
SO SHE CAN GET MARRIED.

13:22.013 --> 13:25.016
OH. BERT, HEY, BUDDY.
I'M SORRY.

13:25.016 --> 13:27.022
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE THEY'LL JUST DO IT.

13:27.022 --> 13:30.021
[ SIGHS ]

13:30.021 --> 13:31.036
HE'S LUCKY
TO HAVE A BROTHER LIKE ME.

13:31.036 --> 13:34.040
[ CLICKING ]

13:34.040 --> 13:37.043
PETE, YOU'VE BEEN DOING THIS
FOR THE PAST 10 MINUTES.

13:37.043 --> 13:39.035
IT'S A BIG SCHOOL.

13:39.035 --> 13:41.044
WE'LL GET SOMEONE'S
ATTENTION EVENTUALLY.

13:43.049 --> 13:44.049
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

13:44.049 --> 13:47.038
I SHOULD BE DRUNK
AND EATING SNAILS RIGHT NOW.

13:47.038 --> 13:49.046
WELL, YOU CAN BLAME DIANE
FOR THAT.

13:49.046 --> 13:51.058
OH, REALLY? YOU WANT TO
BLAME DIANE FOR THAT?

13:51.058 --> 13:53.056
JACKIE HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT.

13:55.061 --> 13:57.048
YOU THINK
THIS IS MY FAULT?

13:57.063 --> 13:59.070
MY FAULT? HOW IS ‐‐
HOW IS THIS MY FAULT?

13:59.070 --> 14:03.065
PETE, WE HAD PLANS TONIGHT
AND YOU LET DIANE CHANGE THEM.

14:03.065 --> 14:05.071
YEAH, BUT YOU ‐‐ YOU ‐‐
YOU HEARD THAT GUILT TRIP

14:05.071 --> 14:08.060
SHE LAID ON ME
ABOUT WARREN AND HILLARY.

14:08.060 --> 14:09.075
HON, THERE'S ALWAYS SOMETHING
WITH DIANE.

14:09.075 --> 14:12.074
SOMETHING ABOUT THE KIDS
OR SOME FATAL KNEE SURGERY,

14:12.074 --> 14:14.085
WHICH, BY THE WAY, I STILL
DON'T BELIEVE IS A REAL THING.

14:14.085 --> 14:16.073
I'VE BEEN DEALING WITH DIANE
FOR A LONG TIME.

14:16.073 --> 14:17.088
YOU START ARGUING
WITH HER ABOUT ONE THING,

14:17.088 --> 14:20.072
PRETTY SOON YOU'RE ARGUING
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

14:20.072 --> 14:21.093
BETTER TO AVOID IT.
BELIEVE ME.

14:21.093 --> 14:23.085
OH, IT'S EASIER TO AVOID IT?
REALLY?

14:23.085 --> 14:25.078
AND IT'S BETTER
TO BE STUCK IN HERE

14:25.078 --> 14:27.092
WITH YOUR LITTLE
ELECTRICAL EXPERIMENT?

14:27.092 --> 14:28.093
I MEAN, LIKE, "OOH!
OH, LET ME TRY.

14:28.093 --> 14:30.092
HERE. HELLO?
IS IT WORKING NOW?"

14:30.092 --> 14:33.107
HELLO?
SOMEONE'S IN HERE.

14:33.107 --> 14:35.103
OKAY. WHAT DO
YOU WANT ME TO DO?

14:35.103 --> 14:37.091
WHAT WOULD I LIKE YOU
TO DO?

14:37.091 --> 14:38.101
I WOULD LIKE FOR YOU
TO STAND UP TO HER.

14:38.101 --> 14:40.103
I WOULD LIKE
FOR YOU TO SAY NO SOMETIMES.

14:40.103 --> 14:43.111
I WOULD LIKE TO NOT PEE ON
A SPONGE AND IN A REAL TOILET.

14:43.111 --> 14:46.098
I WOULD LIKE FOR YOU
TO GET ME OUT OF HERE NOW.

14:46.098 --> 14:47.115
FINE.

14:47.115 --> 14:48.117
[ SIGHS ]

14:48.117 --> 14:50.114
DIANE:
CHILDHOOD OBESITY ‐‐

14:50.114 --> 14:52.115
[ SWITCHES CLICK ]

14:52.115 --> 14:54.123
EXCUSE ME? HELLO?
THE LIGHTS HAVE GONE OUT.

14:54.123 --> 14:56.120
WOMAN: I WISH YOUR MIKE
WOULD GO OUT!

14:56.120 --> 14:58.123
EXCUSE ME. I CAN HEAR YOU.

14:58.123 --> 15:01.128
[ SIGHS ]
I HATE THESE FUNDRAISERS.

15:05.121 --> 15:06.122
PETE:
YOU STILL MAD AT ME?

15:06.122 --> 15:07.128
KATE:
NO, I'M REALLY HAPPY.

15:07.128 --> 15:08.139
THIS TURNED OUT TO BE
A REALLY NICE TIME.

15:08.139 --> 15:10.131
ARE YOU BEING SARCASTIC?
I CAN'T TELL.

15:10.131 --> 15:12.141
IT'S TOO DARK IN ‐‐

15:12.141 --> 15:14.142
OH. GEEZ.

15:14.142 --> 15:16.145
YOU KNOW, PETE.

15:16.145 --> 15:20.148
I GUESS I WAS JUST REALLY
EXCITED ABOUT SPENDING

15:20.148 --> 15:23.138
SOME GROWNUP TIME
WITH MY HUSBAND ‐‐ THAT'S ALL.

15:23.138 --> 15:27.161
KATE...
THIS IS MY SINCERE FACE.

15:27.161 --> 15:29.157
NOTHING ‐‐
[ GASPS ]

15:29.157 --> 15:31.145
OH, MY GOD!

15:31.145 --> 15:32.156
THANK YOU SO MUCH!

15:32.156 --> 15:35.163
GO! GO!
I HAVE TO PEE!
THANK YOU SO MUCH!

15:35.163 --> 15:38.151
YEAH, WE CAME IN HERE
TO GET SOME CUPS

15:38.151 --> 15:39.168
AND THE DOOR
SLAMMED BEHIND US.
WRONG WAY. IT'S THIS WAY.

15:39.168 --> 15:41.166
I HAD TO
JIMMY THE LOCK.

15:41.166 --> 15:44.158
I KNOW HOW TO JIMMY,
BUT THE DOOR HAS A DESIGN FLAW,

15:44.158 --> 15:46.169
SO I HAD TO ‐‐
IS THIS YOURS?

15:46.169 --> 15:47.179
OH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
MY LICENSE.

15:47.179 --> 15:49.169
UH, YOU MIGHT
WANT TO ZIP UP YOUR FLY.

15:49.169 --> 15:51.179
OH, YOU KNOW WHAT ‐‐
MY HANDS ARE FULL.

15:51.179 --> 15:54.177
DO YOU MI‐‐ I GOT IT.

15:54.177 --> 15:57.175
OKAY.
ARE YOU SURE
YOU CAN'T SEE MY HOO‐HA?

15:57.175 --> 15:58.185
OKAY, JACKIE.
MM‐HMM.

15:58.185 --> 15:59.190
YOU PROMISED ME THAT YOU
WOULD IGNORE YOUR INSTINCTS.

15:59.190 --> 16:01.188
SO, NO BEAT‐BOXING?

16:01.188 --> 16:03.194
WE'RE JUST ‐‐
I'M NOT GONNA ‐‐ OKAY.
NO.

16:03.194 --> 16:07.192
AND IN FIVE,
FOUR, THREE...

16:08.194 --> 16:09.198
...ONE!
[ CAMCORDER BEEPS ]

16:09.198 --> 16:12.202
HI. I'M JACKIE.

16:12.202 --> 16:13.207
ARE YOU LOOKING
TO SHARE YOUR LIFE

16:13.207 --> 16:15.205
WITH SOMEONE
AND LEARN IKEBANA,

16:15.205 --> 16:18.203
THE JAPANESE ART
OF FLOWER ARRANGEMENT?

16:18.203 --> 16:19.208
[ RAPID FOOTSTEPS ]
OR MAY‐‐

16:19.208 --> 16:22.213
YEAH! NOODLE DANCE!
OH, YEAH!
CUT!

16:22.213 --> 16:23.217
HEY, WE'RE WORKING
ON SOMETHING HERE,

16:23.217 --> 16:25.212
SO DO YOU MIND GOING
ON THE OTHER SIDE OF THE CAMERA?

16:25.212 --> 16:26.218
I JUST WANTED TO SEE

16:26.218 --> 16:29.207
IF YOU WANTED TO DO
THE NOODLE DANCE WITH ME.

16:29.207 --> 16:30.217
YELLOW?
WELL, I LOVE
THE NOODLE DANCE.

16:30.217 --> 16:33.227
BUT LET ME FINISH UP HERE,
AND THEN I'M ALL YOURS.
FINE.

16:33.227 --> 16:35.221
OKAY, AND I GUESS
THAT WE'LL JUST PICK UP

16:35.221 --> 16:36.226
FROM WHERE WE LEFT OFF,
ALL RIGHT?

16:36.226 --> 16:39.229
OKAY.
AND...ACTION.

16:39.229 --> 16:43.219
FIVE, FOUR, THREE...

16:43.219 --> 16:44.230
TO ME.

16:44.230 --> 16:47.224
OR MAYBE MUSIC IS WHERE
YOUR INTERESTS LIE.

16:47.224 --> 16:49.240
HELLO!
WHAT DOES A GUY HAVE TO DO

16:49.240 --> 16:51.228
TO GET A COOKIE
AROUND HERE?
[ CAMCORDER BEEPS ]

16:51.228 --> 16:53.227
CAN JUST SOMEONE
GET THE KID A COOKIE?

16:53.227 --> 16:55.243
BERTIE‐BOO, DO YOU MIND?
YES, I MIND.

16:55.243 --> 16:58.241
I HATE YOUR DUMB MOVIE, AND
YOU LOOK WEIRD IN THOSE CLOTHES.

16:58.241 --> 17:00.233
[ GASPS ]

17:00.233 --> 17:01.254
OKAY, BERTIE.

17:01.254 --> 17:03.247
THIS IS WHY
I NEVER WORK WITH KIDS.

17:03.247 --> 17:05.254
THEY HAVE NO WORK ETHIC.
I KNOW.

17:05.254 --> 17:09.244
HEY, LET'S HEAR IT
FOR OUR SENIOR CLASS LEADERS,

17:09.244 --> 17:12.257
WHO SPOKE SO PASSIONATELY
ABOUT THE NEEDS OF OUR SCHOOL.

17:12.257 --> 17:17.257
I HAVE TO SAY, THE HAIKU ABOUT
THE RE‐PAVED PARKING LOT ‐‐

17:17.257 --> 17:19.259
THAT WILL STAY WITH ME.

17:19.259 --> 17:22.267
SO, THANK YOU
TO MOST OF YOU.

17:22.267 --> 17:24.263
[ APPLAUSE ]

17:24.263 --> 17:27.271
YOU WANT TO STAY
AND HAVE A DRINK?
NOPE. NOT REALLY.

17:27.271 --> 17:29.264
I JUST WANT
THIS NIGHT TO BE OVER.

17:29.264 --> 17:30.277
DIANE: PETER!

17:33.266 --> 17:34.279
ONE SECOND.

17:34.279 --> 17:36.273
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

17:36.273 --> 17:37.284
FINALLY.

17:37.284 --> 17:39.282
THERE'S JUST
ONE MORE THING I NEED ‐‐
NO.

17:39.282 --> 17:40.288
BUT I NEED ‐‐
NO.

17:40.288 --> 17:42.286
PETER, I NEED YOUR HELP
FOR ONE MINUTE.

17:42.286 --> 17:44.278
NO. THE ANSWER IS NO.

17:44.278 --> 17:45.299
BUT, PETER, I NEED YOU ‐‐
DIANE, NO.

17:45.299 --> 17:47.283
KATE AND I
HAD PLANS TONIGHT.

17:47.283 --> 17:48.299
I ‐‐ I LET YOU STEAMROLL ME
INTO CHANGING THEM,

17:48.299 --> 17:51.285
LIKE YOU ALWAYS DO,
BUT FROM NOW ON,

17:51.285 --> 17:52.292
OUR PLANS COME FIRST,

17:52.292 --> 17:54.305
SO WHATEVER IT IS YOU WANT ME
TO DO, DO IT YOURSELF.

17:54.305 --> 17:56.292
FAIR ENOUGH.

17:56.292 --> 17:59.309
JASON.

17:59.309 --> 18:02.312
APPARENTLY,
PETER IS UNWILLING TO HELP ME

18:02.312 --> 18:06.306
LIFT YOU ONTO THE STAGE
FOR THE COMMEMORATIVE PHOTO.

18:06.306 --> 18:10.302
SO, I'LL JUST HAVE TO FIND
SOMEONE ELSE TO HELP ME.

18:10.302 --> 18:12.303
PATTY! GRAB A WHEEL!

18:12.303 --> 18:14.327
[ THUD ]
WE'RE GOING TO
LIFT HIM ONSTAGE.

18:14.327 --> 18:16.315
BABE, THANK YOU.
YOU'RE MY HERO.

18:16.315 --> 18:18.331
BUT MAYBE YOU SHOULD SAY YES
JUST ONE LAST TIME.

18:18.331 --> 18:20.326
YEAH.

18:20.326 --> 18:21.330
GRABBING A WHEEL.

18:21.330 --> 18:23.314
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

18:23.314 --> 18:25.320
BERT: I'M NOT HERE!

18:25.320 --> 18:28.337
WELL, THAT'S TOO BAD,
BECAUSE I BROUGHT

18:28.337 --> 18:32.343
ONE OF YOUR FAVORITE PEOPLE
HERE TO SEE YOU.

18:32.343 --> 18:34.344
[ AS CHRISTOPHER WALKEN ]
BERT.

18:34.344 --> 18:36.337
I‐I DON'T UNDERSTAND

18:36.337 --> 18:40.331
WHY YOU WON'T OPEN
THIS DOOR FOR ME.

18:40.331 --> 18:42.348
THAT'S CRAZY. UH...

18:42.348 --> 18:46.355
I CAN NEVER RESIST
YOUR CHRISTOPHER WALKEN.
NOBODY CAN.

18:47.355 --> 18:49.355
WHAT'S UP?

18:49.355 --> 18:52.350
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO GET MARRIED.

18:52.350 --> 18:54.353
OH, WELL, WHO SAID
ANYTHING ABOUT MARRIAGE?

18:54.353 --> 18:55.368
HEY, I'M JUST HOPING
TO MEET SOMEONE

18:55.368 --> 18:58.352
THAT I CAN
HANG OUT WITH.

18:58.352 --> 19:00.363
BUT WHAT ABOUT ME?
WHY CAN'T WE HANG OUT?

19:00.363 --> 19:02.374
OH, WE CAN ALWAYS HANG OUT,
AND WE DO,

19:02.374 --> 19:05.376
BUT I ALSO NEED TO SPEND TIME
WITH SOMEONE MY OWN AGE.

19:05.376 --> 19:08.364
I KEEP READING
"PERCY JACKSON,"

19:08.364 --> 19:10.382
EVEN AFTER YOU'VE GONE TO BED,
AND THAT'S NOT RIGHT.

19:10.382 --> 19:13.366
BUT IF YOU MEET SOMEONE,

19:13.366 --> 19:15.383
I WON'T BE YOUR
NUMBER‐ONE GUY ANYMORE.

19:15.383 --> 19:17.370
OHH! BERT!

19:17.370 --> 19:18.391
OKAY, NOW,
YOU LISTEN TO ME.

19:18.391 --> 19:20.393
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,

19:20.393 --> 19:24.392
YOU WILL ALWAYS BE
MY NUMBER‐ONE GUY.

19:24.392 --> 19:26.392
OKAY?

19:26.392 --> 19:29.388
I PROMISE. MWAH.

19:29.388 --> 19:31.390
AND I DON'T HATE
YOUR OUTFIT.

19:31.390 --> 19:34.397
I'VE JUST NEVER
SEEN YOUR LEGS BEFORE.

19:34.397 --> 19:36.404
PETE: TA‐DA!

19:36.404 --> 19:38.406
[ GASPS ]
WHAT'S THIS?

19:38.406 --> 19:40.407
A ROMANTIC DINNER
FOR TWO.

19:40.407 --> 19:41.409
I HAVE AN IN
WITH THE CHEF.

19:41.409 --> 19:43.402
WOW.
YEAH.

19:43.402 --> 19:45.399
IS HE 8 AND CHINESE?

19:45.399 --> 19:48.406
UH, NO,
HE'S 15 AND UNUSUAL.

19:48.406 --> 19:50.407
LET'S SEE
WHAT WE HAVE.

19:50.407 --> 19:52.413
OOH, DINO NUGGETS

19:52.413 --> 19:54.423
WITH A TRIO
OF DIPPING SAUCES ‐‐

19:54.423 --> 19:58.419
RANCH, BARBECUE,
AND...PEANUT BUTTER.

19:58.419 --> 19:59.432
GOOD CHOICE.
CHUNKY.

19:59.432 --> 20:01.420
TO CLEANSE YOUR PALATE,
I CAN OFFER YOU

20:01.420 --> 20:02.423
A CHOICE
OF FRUIT LEATHER.

20:02.423 --> 20:06.422
WE HAVE VERY BERRY CHERRY
AND PURPLE.

20:06.422 --> 20:08.438
SURPRISE ME.
VERY GOOD.

20:08.438 --> 20:12.433
AND FOR DESSERT,
WE HAVE WHISKEY.

20:12.433 --> 20:13.444
I'LL START
WITH DESSERT.

20:13.444 --> 20:18.431
I'M SORRY ABOUT TONIGHT.
IT'S NOT EXACTLY VOULOIR.

20:18.431 --> 20:19.446
THIS IS ALL I WANTED.

20:19.446 --> 20:22.450
JUST YOU, ME,
SOME ANIMAL‐SHAPED FOOD,

20:22.450 --> 20:25.447
AND A BUTT‐LOAD
OF WHISKEY.
[ SIGHS ]

20:25.447 --> 20:27.448
KISS ME.

20:27.448 --> 20:30.456
AW, LOOK AT THAT.
THAT'S CUTE. KISSY‐KISSY.

20:30.456 --> 20:31.462
[ GASPS ]
DINO NUGGETS!

20:31.462 --> 20:34.463
I NEED ONE FOR THE ROAD.
AND HE NEEDS A FRIEND.

20:34.463 --> 20:35.468
GOOD. MMM. YUM.
DIP SAUCE.

20:35.468 --> 20:37.466
GOOD, GOOD.
HELP YOURSELF.

20:37.466 --> 20:39.457
ALL RIGHT.
A LITTLE OVER‐NUKED, BUT GOOD.

20:39.457 --> 20:40.471
IS SHE WEARING
OUR BEDSPREAD?

20:43.468 --> 20:45.465
OH, HELLO!

20:45.465 --> 20:47.460
I DIDN'T
SEE YOU THERE.

20:47.460 --> 20:49.476
MY NAME IS BERT.
AND I'M JACKIE.

20:49.476 --> 20:52.470
AND THIS HERE
IS MY NUMBER‐ONE GUY.

20:52.470 --> 20:55.472
BUT I'M ALSO LOOKING
FOR A REAL SOLID NUMBER TWO.

20:55.472 --> 20:58.476
SO, IF YOU'RE THE TYPE OF GUY
THAT'S INTO ECSTATIC DANCE...

20:58.476 --> 20:59.491
AND LICORICE!

20:59.491 --> 21:01.478
OH,
AND GREEN‐TEA ENEMAS.

21:01.478 --> 21:02.490
OOH, AND FROGS!

21:02.490 --> 21:04.483
AND SHIATSU.

21:04.483 --> 21:08.489
